data.title: The Collective Developed Games
data.meta_description: The Collective was a division of Foundation 9 Entertainment, now the company has been merged with Shiny Entertainment to create Double Helix Games.
data.text:
The Da Vinci Code

April 14, 2006

PS2

XBOX

PC

Play through the events of the controversial novel in this game that was timed with the release of the movie.

Marc Ecko's Getting Up: Contents Under Pressure

February 14, 2006

PS2

XBOX

PC

Getting Up is a video game created by Atari and the Collective. It revolves around the main character, a punk named Trane, as he tries to take back the city of New Radius through the medium of vandalism.

Star Wars: Episode III - Revenge of the Sith

May 4, 2004

GBA

PS2

+ 3 more

XBOX

DS

PS3N

An action-adventure adaptation of the final film in the Star Wars prequel trilogy, detailing both the fall of the Separatist movement and the rise of Anakin's betrayal into Darth Vader.

Wrath Unleashed

February 9, 2004

PS2

XBOX

Archon-like, Wrath Unleashed features strategic hex-based maneuvering followed by 3D combat in order to control territory and defeat the opposing side. The objective is to crush the enemy completely or vanquish their god.

Star Trek: Deep Space Nine - The Fallen

August 1, 2001

MAC

PC

Star Trek Deep Space Nine: The Fallen is a third person shooter based on the Deep Space Nine series that was released in the year 2000 PC and Mac.

Men in Black: The Game

November 1997

PS1

PC

RZON

A loosely video game adaptation of the 1997 film of the same name into an action/adventure game similar to Resident Evil.

Dirty Harry

X360

PS3

Dirty Harry (working title) was a game cited as coming to the Xbox360 and PS3, however the game has been significantly delayed and subsequently cancelled due to problems with the developer. Warner Bros. Interactive still intend to produce the game at a later date.
